{
  "created": {
    "descriptionHtml": "<p>A new instance of a previously detected secret was detected in a repository, and the location of the secret was added to the existing alert.</p>",
    "summaryHtml": "<p>This event occurs when there is activity relating to the locations of a secret in a secret scanning alert.</p>\n<p>For more information about secret scanning, see \"<a href=\"https://docs.github.com/enterprise-server@3.21/code-security/secret-scanning/about-secret-scanning\">About secret scanning</a>.\" For information about the API to manage secret scanning alerts, see \"<a href=\"https://docs.github.com/enterprise-server@3.21/rest/secret-scanning\">Secret scanning</a>\" in the REST API documentation.</p>\n<p>For activity relating to secret scanning alerts, use the <code>secret_scanning_alert</code> event.</p>\n<p>To subscribe to this event, a GitHub App must have at least read-level access for the \"Secret scanning alerts\" repository permission.</p>",
